Section 5.5

In this section, we learn to add and subtract polynomials. In particular, we learn to be especially careful when subtracting polynomials.

Please note that I will not require you to use the so-called "vertical format" to add or subtract polynomials. Indeed, I encourage you to master operating on polynomials horizontally.

YouTube Video Example:

[(4x^2) + 5x + 7] + [(3x^2) - 8x + 12] =
(7x^2) - 3x + 19

[(9x^2) - 7x + 13] - [(5x^2) - 7x - 14] = 
(9x^2) - 7x + 13 - (5x^2) + 7x + 14 = 
(4x^2) + 27


[(3x^3) - 5x + 8] - [(7x^2) + 6x - 9] = 
(3x^3) - 5x + 8 - (7x^2) - 6x + 9 = 
(3x^3) - (7x^2) - 11x + 17





*************************************************************************************************

Section 5.6

In this section, we learn to multiply polynomials and how to apply products of polynomials to solve problems.

* As you read this section's narrative, pay special attention to the multiplication method in subsection 3 called FOIL. Pay attention also to the multiplication method in subsection 4 and illustrated in Examples 6 and 7. Some instructors call this method "each by every" but I like to call it SuperFOIL! (Example 7 illustrates the so-called "vertical" format for multiplying polynomials; however, I urge you to master the horizontal format. The vertical format is like riding a bicycle with training wheels. Which, by the way, I did for several months, much to my father's horror.)
* Do the odd-numbered Guided Practice exercises and as many of the Try-It-Yourself exercises as you can. Be sure to include some with fractions (like #87 and 89) and some with trinomials (like #101 and 103).



Use SuperFOIL to multiply: [(x^2) + 2xy + (2y^2)][(x^2) - 2xy + (2y^2)]

[(x^2) + 2xy + (2y^2)][(x^2) - 2xy + (2y^2)] = 

(x^2)(x^2) - (x^2)(2xy) + (x^2)(2y^2) + (2xy)(x^2) - (2xy)(2xy) + (2xy)(2y^2) + (2y^2)(x^2) - (2y^2)(2xy) + (2y^2)(2y^2) = 

(x^4) - (2x^3y) + (2x^2y^2) + (2x^3y) - (4x^2y^2) + (4xy^3) + (2x^2y^2) - (4xy^3) + (4y^4) =

(x^4) + (4y^4)

*************************************************************************************************

