Division

Example: [(x^2) + 7x + 12] / (x + 3) =
[(x+3)(x+4)] / (x+3) = 
x + 4



Long Division with a Trinomial

Example: [(2x^2) - x + 6] / (x - 2)

Step 1: (2x^2) / (x) = 2x

2x * -2 = -4x
[(2x^2) - x] - [(2x^2) - 4x] = 3x
(3x + 6) / (x - 2)

Step 2: (-3x) / (x) = -3

(-3) * (-2) = 6
(-3x + 6) - (-3x + 6) = 0

Answers gathered from Steps = 2x - 3

**********************************************




Another way to solve this example: 

[(2x^2) - x + 6] / (x - 2) = 2x - 3

x - 2 = 0
x = 2

2 * | 2 |     -7       |       6       |
             (2*2)=4    (2*-3)=-6
                 4              -6
     ———————————-
        2      -3               0

Answer: 2x - 3  Remainder 0
        




